#######################################INSTRUCTIONS########################################
cd ./solution --> compute the excess solvation free energy of naphthalene in water via the cavity method
cd ./solid --> compute the absolute Helmholtz free energy of naphthalene crystal via the extended Einstein crystal method

Examples are for the ambient pressure p = 1 atm and temperature T = 298 K.
Experimental data are provided for p = 0.1 MPa. 
Pressure in LAMMPS "real units" is expressed in atm. In the present work, the authors have neglected the small difference between 1 atm = 1.013E+5 Pa and 0.1 MPa = 1E+5 Pa, using the approximation that “1 atm ≈ 0.1 MPa” in all comparisons.
###########################################################################################
For further details and instructions of how to compute these free energies

read "./solid/Readme_solid"

read "./solution/Readme_solution"
###########################################################################################
